'''Hukawng Valley Tiger Reserve''' ({{lang-my|ဟူကောင်း ကျား ထိန်းသိမ်းရေး နယ်မြေ}} {{IPA-my|hùkáʊɴ tɕá tʰéɪɴ θéɪɴ jé nɛ̀ mjè|}}) is a wildlife reserve located in [[Hukawng Valley]], near [[Tanai]] in [[Myitkyina District]] of [[Kachin State]], [[Burma]] (Myanmar). Hukawng Valley Tiger Reserve covers 21890&nbsp;km². The Burmese government has also designated 6500&nbsp;km² of the valley as the protected forest reserve. It is the world's largest tiger reserve.<ref name=bw>{{cite journal | title=Only 50 tigers left in Hukaung valley, world largest tiger reserve | author=Kyaw Zeya | work=Bi-Weekly Eleven | date=2010-10-15 | publisher=Weekly Eleven News | language=Burmese | page=7 | volume=3 | number=32}}</ref>

According to a report by the [[Wildlife Conservation Society]] released in October 2010, only 50 tigers remain in Hukawng valley. The reserve also consists of 35 kinds of mammals such as [[Indochinese tiger]], [[Indochinese leopard]], [[Indian elephant]], [[bear]] and species of [[Old World monkey|monkey]]s, over 370 species of birds, 46 species of frogs, 37 species of fresh water fish, four species of turtle, species of butterflies and 13,500 plant species.<ref name=bw/>

The Wildlife Conservation Society has been criticized for its role in the reserve, particularly in [[Victim blaming|blaming]] [[indigenous peoples]] for environmental damage despite evidence that [[gold mining]] in the reserve is devastating the tigers' [[habitat]].<ref name=kachinnews>{{cite web | title=Gold Mining expands in Burma's Hugawng "Tiger Reserve" | date=27 August 2012 | publisher=KNG |url=http://www.kachinnews.com/news/2385-gold-mining-expands-in-burma-s-hugawng-tiger-reserve.html}}</ref>  More than 200,000 acres of land in Hukawng Valley are being used for gold mining, causing environmental damage.<ref name=BNI>{{cite web | title=Than Shwe urged to stop land grab in Hukawng Valley tiger reserve | date=17 August 2007 | publisher=Burma News International | url=http://bnionline.net/feature/narinjara/2265-than-shwe-urged-to-stop-land-grab-in-hukawng-valley-tiger-reserve.html | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140109071642/http://bnionline.net/feature/narinjara/2265-than-shwe-urged-to-stop-land-grab-in-hukawng-valley-tiger-reserve.html | archivedate=9 January 2014 | df= }}</ref>

