==Ireland==
The rules of [[Irish orthography|Irish Gaelic spelling]] are different from those of English. Most Irish places have English names originating as anglicised spellings of Irish names. Placenames with gaelicised or unanglicised spellings (such as '''[[Cóbh]]''', [[County Cork]] – {{IPAc-en|ˈ|k|oʊ|v}} ''Cóbh''<ref name=wells />) are omitted.

Ending ''-ane'' is regularly pronounced {{IPAc-en|ɑː|n}}, with PALM vowel rather than FACE vowel, as in [[Ferbane]], [[Portrane]], [[Strabane]], [[Teebane bombing|Teebane]].  ''-agh'' is pronounced {{IPAc-en|ɑː}}, with a silent 'g'. ''Innis-'' is generally pronounced  {{IPAc-en|ˈ|ɪ|n|ɪ|ʃ}}.

* '''[[Aghabullogue]]''', [[County Cork]] – {{IPAc-en|æ|ˈ|h|æ|b|ʌ|l|ʌ|ɡ}}
* '''[[Ahoghill]]''', [[County Antrim]] – {{IPAc-en|æ|ˈ|h|ɒ|k|ɪ|l}} or {{IPAc-en|æ|ˈ|h|ɒ|x|ɪ|l}}
* '''[[Athy]]''', [[County Kildare]] – {{IPAc-en|æ|ˈ|θ|aɪ}} 
* '''Boyounagh''', [[County Galway]] –  {{IPAc-en|ˈ|b|w|iː|n|ə|x}}
* '''[[Breaghwy]]''', [[Connacht]] –  {{IPAc-en|ˈ|b|r|eɪ|f|iː}} 
