==Wales==
Similarly, the [[Welsh language]] has its own rules, which a large proportion of Welsh settlements follow.
Commonly mispronounced names, due to exceptions from either set of rules are:
* '''[[Denbigh]]''', [[Wales]] – {{IPAc-en|d|ɛ|n|b|i}}<ref name=wells /> <!--silent -gh may be regular but -igh normally is /aɪ/ as in bight, penlight, superhigh, or sigh --><!-- Indeed - this is normally instead eigh.-->
* '''[[Goodwick]]''', [[Pembrokeshire]] – {{IPAc-en|ˈ|ɡ|ʊ|d|ɪ|k}}
* '''[[Hawarden]]''', [[Flintshire]] – {{IPAc-en|ˈ|h|ɑːr|d|ən}}<ref name=wells />
* '''[[Holyhead]]''', Holy Island, [[Anglesey]] – {{IPAc-en|ˈ|h|ɒ|l|i|h|ɛ|d}}<ref name=wells />
* '''[[Laugharne]]''', [[Carmarthenshire]] – {{IPAc-en|ˈ|l|ɑːr|n}}<ref name=wells />
* '''[[Swansea]]''' – {{IPAc-en|'|s|w|ɒ|n|z|i}}

