{{short description|A peninsula with narrow connection to mainland}} {{Unreferenced|auto=yes|date=December 2009}} [[File:Velez de la Gomera.jpg|thumb|Peñón de Vélez de la Gomera, Spain]]'''Presque-isle''' (from the [[French language|French]] ''presqu'île'', meaning ''almost island'') is a geographical term denoting a piece of land which is closer to being an [[island]] than most [[peninsula]]s because of its being joined to the mainland by an extremely narrow neck of land.
[[Image:Presqu'ile de Quiberon.png|right|thumbnail|260px|The Presque-isle of [[Quiberon]], [[France]]]]
==List of presque-Isles== *[[Peñón de Vélez de la Gomera]] in [[Spain]] *[[Monte Argentario]] in [[Italy]] *[[Quiberon]] in [[Brittany]], [[France]] *[[Saint-Malo]] in [[Brittany]], [[France]] *[[Mahia Peninsula]] in the [[North Island]] of [[New Zealand]] *[[Presqu'ile Provincial Park]] in [[Ontario]], [[Canada]] *[[Presque Isle State Park]] in [[Erie, Pennsylvania]], [[United States]] *[[Presque Isle Township, Michigan|Presque Isle Township]] in [[Presque Isle County, Michigan]] *[[Catawba Island Township, Ottawa County, Ohio]] *[[Presque Isle Park]], Marquette, Michigan *[[Presque Isle, Maine|Presque Isle]] in [[Maine]], [[United States]] *[[Presqu'ile (Lyon)|Presque-isle of Lyon]], (name used for the 1st and 2de arrondissements of [[Lyon]] between the rivers Rhône and Saône. {{Expand list|date=August 2008}}
==See also== * [[Presque Isle (disambiguation)|Presque Isle]]
