{{Infobox country telephone plan | country = Canada | country_link = Canada | continent = North America | map_image = | map_caption = | map_size = | map_alt = | country_calling_code = +1 | international_prefix = 011 | trunk_prefix = 1 | regulator = | plan_membership = | nsn_length = | dial_plan_type = | number_format = | codes_list = }}
'''Telephone numbers in Canada''' follow the fixed-length [[Bell System]] format, consisting of the [[List of country calling codes|country code]] +1, followed by a three-digit [[numbering plan area|area code]], a three-digit [[telephone exchange|central office code]] (or exchange code) and a four-digit station code. This is represented as 1 NPA NXX-XXXX,<ref>http://www.btb.termiumplus.gc.ca/tpv2guides/guides/favart/index-fra.html?lang=fra&lettr=indx_autr8SPbfCcS_FFE&page=9N6fM9QmOwCE.html</ref> in which the [[List of country calling codes|country code]] is "1".
Local calls from Canadian landlines must be dialled without the leading '1', which is used as the [[trunk prefix]] for domestic long distance calls. Toll calls from Canada to other [[North American Numbering Plan]] countries are dialled in the same format (eleven digits) as domestic calls. Overseas calls to locations outside country code +1 are dialled with the '''011''' [[List of international call prefixes|international prefix]], followed by the country code and the national significant number.
{| class="wikitable" ! Province / Territory !! Codes ([[overlay plan|Overlays]] in Italic) |- | [[Alberta]] || [[Area code 403|403]], ''[[Area code 587 and 825|587]]'', [[Area code 780|780]], ''[[Area code 587 and 825|825]]'' |- | [[British Columbia]] || ''[[Area code 236|236]]'', [[Area code 250|250]], [[Area code 604|604]], ''[[Area code 778|778]]'' |- | [[Manitoba]] || [[Area codes 204 and 431|204]], ''[[Area codes 204 and 431|431]]'' |- | [[New Brunswick]] || [[Area code 506|506]] |- | [[Newfoundland and Labrador]] || [[Area code 709|709]] |- | [[Nova Scotia]] and [[Prince Edward Island]] || [[Area code 902|902]], ''[[Area codes 902 and 782|782]]'' |- | [[Ontario]] || ''[[Area codes 519 and 226|226]]'', ''[[Area codes 705 and 249|249]]'', ''[[Area codes 905, 289 and 365|289]]'', ''[[Area codes 613 and 343|343]]'', ''[[Area codes 905, 289 and 365|365]]'', [[Area codes 416, 647 and 437|416]], ''[[Area codes 416, 647 and 437|437]]'', [[Area codes 519 and 226|519]], ''[[Area codes 519, 226, and 548|548]]'', [[Area codes 613 and 343|613]], ''[[Area codes 416, 647 and 437|647]]'', [[Area codes 705 and 249|705]], [[Area code 807|807]], [[Area codes 905, 289 and 365|905]] |- | [[Quebec]] || [[Area codes 418 and 581|418]], ''[[Area codes 514 and 438|438]]'', [[Area codes 450 and 579|450]], [[Area codes 514 and 438|514]], ''[[Area codes 450 and 579|579]]'', ''[[Area codes 418 and 581|581]]'', [[Area codes 819 and 873|819]], ''[[Area codes 819 and 873|873]]'' |- | [[Saskatchewan]] || [[Area codes 306 and 639|306]], ''[[Area codes 306 and 639|639]]'' |- | [[Yukon]], [[Northwest Territories]] and [[Nunavut]] || [[Area code 867|867]] |}
== Mobile phones == As the recipient of a mobile call pays airtime, standard [[mobile phone]] numbers are not uniquely different from land-line numbers and thus follow the same format and area codes as for land-lines. Numbers may be [[local number portability|ported between landline and mobile]]. The rarely used non-geographic [[area code 600]] is one exception to this pattern (non-portable, and allows caller-pays-airtime [[satellite phone|satellite telephony]]); some [[independent telephone company|independent]] landline exchanges are also non-portable.
Mobile phone providers had supported either [[IS-95|CDMA]] or [[GSM]]; both are being supplanted by [[Universal Mobile Telecommunications System|UMTS]]. [[Telus Mobility|Telus]] shut down its CDMA in mid-2015; [[Bell Mobility]]'s CDMA network, the country's last major provider of that type, went dark on January 1, 2017.<ref>[http://mobilesyrup.com/2014/04/08/bell-lays-out-plan-to-shutter-its-cdma-network-by-january-1st-2017/ "Bell lays out plan to shutter its CDMA network by January 1st, 2017"]</ref>
== Toll-free and premium numbers == Non-geographic [[toll-free telephone number]]s (+1 800, 833<ref>https://atlc.com/2017/01/17/fcc-announces-release-new-833-toll-free-prefix/ "Announces Release of New 833 Toll Free Prefix"</ref>, 844, 855, 866, 877, 888) and [[premium-rate telephone number]]s (+1-900) are allocated from the same blocks as the corresponding US numbers. Numbers with exchange code +1 NPA 976-XXXX are also expensive premium calls.
