{{Infobox river | name = Vitoshka Bistritsa | image = Bistritsa river 1.JPG | image_size = | image_caption = Vitoshka Bistritsa, near Pancharevo | source1_location = | mouth_location = [[Iskar (river)|Iskar]] | mouth_coordinates = {{coord|42.5964|23.4153|display=it|region:BG_type:river}} | progression = {{RIskar}} | subdivision_type1 = Country | subdivision_name1 = [[Bulgaria]] | length = | source1_elevation = | mouth_elevation = | discharge1_avg = | basin_size = | tributaries_left = | tributaries_right = }} '''Bistritsa''' or '''Vitoshka Bistritsa''' ({{lang-bg|Бистрица; Витошка Бистрица; Бистришка река}}), is a river in western [[Bulgaria]], tributary of [[Iskar River]]. Flows from the eastern slopes of [[Golyam Rezen|Golyam Rezen Peak]] on [[Vitosha|Vitosha Mountain]], crossing [[Bistrishko Branishte]] Nature Reserve, where it forms a small but beautiful waterfall Samokovishteto, then crossing villages of [[Bistritsa, Sofia|Bistritsa]] and [[Pancharevo]] to flow into [[Lake Pancharevo]], near [[Sofia]]. Additional charm of the area offer several [[artificial waterfall]]s in the lower reaches of the river.
